freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: I Have what I believe to be swollen lymph nodes, as the center portion of my chest developed a lump.   The area around it is sore  I am a Hodgkins survivor for 15 years so this is worrisome however my oncologist nurse said vaccine likely caused it.

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Ive had the munchies a lot more. Probably just the isolation.
My shoulder blades started having pain near injection shoulder and worked it way to opposite side. The original shoulder is fine now so Im hoping it will stop soon on opposite side
Shoulder, chest and back pain in area closest to injected shoulder
Soreness in chest I believe its my lymph nodes swelling again as it feels sore and a lump is felt in that area.
